# Google review and testimonials workflow

When the user pastes a Google Maps review or asks to **update testimonial(s)**:

## 0. Skip if already on testimonials page

Before applying a **new** review from a feed/paste, check whether that quote is **already captured** on `new/testimonials.html` (same quote text, or same Google `profileUrl` + quote).

- If yes → **skip** that review (do not re-write config or re-scaffold).
- `node scripts/apply-google-review.mjs` does this automatically; use `--force` to apply anyway.
- `--sync-all` always refreshes all configs and rebuilds the page (no skip).

## 1. Map review → project (human / agent)

Match review text and owner replies to a repair folder under `projects/`. If no folder exists and the repair is real, scaffold a new project (`config.json`, photos later).

Say **unmapped** when the review is general shop praise with no repair (→ standalone only).

**Names:** Never store a full surname in the repo. `authorName` in config is **first name + last initial** only (e.g. `Howard C.`). When pasting from Google, pass `--author "Howard Chung"` — the apply script saves `Howard C.` only. Optional `profileUrl` links the name on testimonials cards.

## 2. Apply with scripts (do not hand-edit HTML when this flow applies)

```bash
# One project — set googleReview, re-scaffold story if index.html exists, rebuild testimonials
node scripts/apply-google-review.mjs <project-id> \
  --author "Reviewer Full Name" \
  --quote "Paste review text from Google." \
  [--profile-url "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/…"]

# Re-apply from config only (after manual config edit)
node scripts/apply-google-review.mjs <project-id> --from-config

# Refresh all project reviews + testimonials page
node scripts/apply-google-review.mjs --sync-all
```

Options:

- `--force` — apply even when the review is already on the testimonials page
- `--no-featured` — keep review on project story only (`featuredOnTestimonials: false`)
- `--no-scaffold` — skip `index.html` regen
- `--no-testimonials` — skip `new/testimonials.html` rebuild

Rebuild testimonials only:

```bash
node scripts/sync-testimonials-html.mjs
node scripts/sync-testimonials-html.mjs --intro "From Google Reviews. Updated on Google Maps, May 2026."
```

If `authorName` was stripped from configs, restore from `data/google-review-author-names.json`:

```bash
node scripts/restore-google-review-author-names.mjs
node scripts/apply-google-review.mjs --sync-all
```

## 3. What each step updates

| Step | File | Result |
|------|------|--------|
| Config | `projects/<folder>/config.json` | `googleReview`: `quote`, `authorName` (partial, e.g. `Howard C.`), optional `profileUrl`, `featuredOnTestimonials`, `featuredOrder` |
| Story | `projects/<folder>/index.html` | `<blockquote class="project-review">` footer `— First L.` |
| Testimonials | `new/testimonials.html` | `— First L.` on its own line (no link; `profileUrl` for dedupe only) |
| Repair link | Testimonials card | If `webpageUrl` or `index.html` exists: **Repair: {title}** → project page |

## 4. `googleReview` schema (canonical)

```json
"googleReview": {
  "quote": "Review text.",
  "authorName": "Howard C.",
  "profileUrl": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/…",
  "featuredOnTestimonials": true,
  "featuredOrder": 53
}
```

Use `null` when there is no review. Legacy keys `author` / `text` are accepted when reading.

## 5. Standalone reviews (no project)

General praise (TV remote, shop overall) with no repair folder → add to `data/testimonials-standalone.json`, then run `sync-testimonials-html.mjs`. Do **not** invent a project config.

## 6. HTML policy

`apply-google-review` and `sync-testimonials-html` **may** write `new/testimonials.html` and regen project `index.html` when the user explicitly requested testimonial / Google review updates. Other HTML still follows the *no HTML unless asked* rule.

## 7. HTML webpage release

When **`publish <id> to webpage`** / **`publish-webpage.mjs`** runs:

1. **Story** — if `index.html` exists and **`googleReview`** is set, syncs the **`<blockquote class="project-review">`** block from config (unless `--no-story-review`). New pages from scaffold include the block automatically.
2. **Testimonials** — if the story is live (`index.html` / `webpageUrl`), rebuilds **`new/testimonials.html`** with a **Repair:** link (unless `--no-testimonials`).

See [`docs/website-go-live.md`](../../docs/website-go-live.md) §3b.

## 8. After apply

- Show which project id was mapped and whether story/testimonials were updated.
- If review mentions a toy not in the map, ask the owner to confirm project id before applying.

